<BR>
Vikings?  You have got to be kidding.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uozaak.showPublicProfile>Ozaak</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/00 2:02:37 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.suvangi.com/~robj/x.gifa WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Taking advantage of the lazy, role playing a rogue and m</span><hr size=1> I pickup a crude stein everytime I go to CT.  They're lore and bouncers spawn decently fast, so the hunters ALWAYS have a stein, so anyone walking by can pick them up.  Selling them for 60 is pretty hard, but 30-40 isn't too bad.  I usually just give them away since I know I'll be getting another soon. <BR>  <BR> my favorite was a lvl 50 was trying to buying ravenscale at a bazaar, and eventually gave me a tell since I was wearing my full suits.  I talk to him awhile about how long it took and about how it sucked because I had to fight all the twinkers to buy em, etc, etc.  Eventually he offers me rubicite legs for my ravenscale legs.  Legs are by far the easiest piece to get, so I accept.  15 minutes later I buy some new ravenscale legs from a twink who is selling off after giving up for 200pp.  Later convert my rubi legs into a very lovely froglock crown for myself and a screaming mace for a friend. <BR>  <BR> Lazy twinks are the best. <p><strong><font size=4 color="#333333"><u>Ozaak Kaazo                                        </u></font><br>
<font size=2 color="#660000">Not all Dwarves are bitter old men... some are dirty too.</font><br>
<font size=3 color="#664400">Bitter, dirty, old Dwarf.  Humble follower of Bristlebane</strong></font><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kilfara>Kilfara</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/00 4:08:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Trading</span><hr size=1> I'm glad to see that such bargaining and trading can happen.  I just got a SBS from the Trainer in CB, and since I'm 1 lvl away from Duel Wield, I'm interested in selling it.  On Solusek Ro, I've seen them sell for around 30-50pp if I recall correctly.  I'll be making a trip soon to Freeport and was hoping to sell it for more or perhaps trade it for something rare to the Kelethin area.  Is that right, 30-50pp? <BR>  <BR> Kilfara <BR> 12th Blade <BR> Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uhalen.showPublicProfile>Halen</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/00 8:21:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trading</span><hr size=1> SBS goes from 10-30pp from what I've seen. <BR>  <BR> Actually the _real_ earner I've had recently is the stein of moggok quest - 2000 plat and rising so far. <BR>  <BR> Last night was good - my ogre picked up some elf hide gloves for 50pp and then swopped them for a bloodstained mantle and a shiny brass halberd. My rogue then swopped a stein of moggok for some ravenscale arms with a guildmate (who gave the stein as a present to another guildmate), paid 200pp for some RS boots from a nice shaman who was going to sell them to a guildmate's twink for 250, and swopped a stein of moggok for a bracer of erollisi! <BR>  <BR> I then handed in my complete drinks collection and got the gem of stamina for the burning rapier quest.... <BR>  <BR> So on the whole, a good night :-)))) <BR>  <BR>  <p><P>Halen Sleet, 21st Barbarian Rogue, Bristlebane

<P>Halen patronises YOU for 128 points of damage...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uswiftberry.showPublicProfile>Swiftberry</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/17/00 1:38:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You gotta think big if your gonna win.</span><hr size=1> I have been buying/selling through out all my levels. I first started in butcherblock. I did errand for all the high level druids there. they gave me the axes (sell for 22p with high charisma and good faction)they let me keep 50% and keep all the fine steel and ringmail armor. I stayed there untill I got some decent armor and about 400p. Now you have to find someone selling serpentine bracers. I have bought them for 150p each before! this is a great money maker. it isn't much now because everyone is selling them. but every now and then you get a sucker to buy them for 300p. One thing, you must give good deals. and be kind to the newbies. I have met soem very kewl people. you never know if you meet a low lvl character and they have a lvl 50 wizard or soemthing. just a word of the wise. My most recent trade. I bought silver plated leggings for 550p!!!! I traded them for a bunch of crap which I got 2000p for. bought me some Dwarven work boots for 1200p. I haven't decided whether i want to sell these or trade. But I always auction them to see if soemone will hook me up for them. Always look for good deals and try to talk people down. I hope my wisdom has helped.<br>
<br>
Swiftberry *Karana Server*<br>
